Class AbstractOpenCVController

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.cshadd.fetch_bot.controllers.AbstractController
      • io.github.cshadd.fetch_bot.controllers.AbstractOpenCVController
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Controller, OpenCVController, FetchBot
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    OpenCVControllerImpl

    public abstract class AbstractOpenCVController
extends AbstractController
implements OpenCVController
    The Class AbstractOpenCVController. Defines what an OpenCV Controller is. An OpenCV Controller is basically a manager for OpenCV tasks in Fetch Bot.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Christian Shadd, Maria Verna Aquino, Thanh Vu, Joseph Damian, Giovanni Orozco

    • Method Detail

      • detections

        protected void detections(org.opencv.core.Mat mat)
        Processes the detections from the matrix from the mat. The mat is loaded from the buffer of frames from the camera thread. The process follows:
        1. Convert the image matrix into a "blob".
        2. Feed "blob" into Caffe neural network.
        3. Detections are outputted as matrix.
        Index Value
        0 Always 0 (?)
        1 Detected object
        2 Confidence level of detection
        3 Starting X coordinate of detection
        4 Starting Y coordinate of detection
        5 Ending X coordinate of detection
        6 Ending Y coordinate of detection

        4. Draw terminals in the terminal for each detection.
        Parameters:
        mat - the mat
